[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmp0c9v1rga[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDuring fuzz testing of the libexif library with the `exif_from_data_fuzzer` [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mharness, AddressSanitizer reported a heap-based buffer overflow in the function [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `src/libexif/libexif/exif-data.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. A specially [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcrafted input caused a `memcpy` to read [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes immediately past a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte heap [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation, triggering ASan’s multi-byte-read-heap-buffer-overflow detection and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maborting execution.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue Type  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  A heap-buffer-overflow [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmulti-byte read[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m was detected by AddressSanitizer. The [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow occurs when `exif_data_load_data_entry` performs a `memcpy` beyond the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounds of a heap buffer.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Key Observations  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. The crash is reported at  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     `__asan_memcpy [0m[35m/src/llvm-project/.../[0m[95masan_interceptors_memintrinsics.cpp[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m63:3[0m[39m`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     invoked by  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     `exif_data_load_data_entry [0m[35m/src/libexif/libexif/[0m[95mexif-data.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m213:3[0m[39m`.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. The offending read is size [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m at address `[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m`, which is [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimmediately after a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte region [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x511000000180[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m allocated [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvia `malloc`.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. The stack trace shows the call sequence:  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • exif_data_load_data_entry → exif_data_load_data_content → [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_data_load_data → exif_data_new_from_data → LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput → libFuzzer [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minternals → `main`.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Where to Investigate  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  To understand the full impact and context of this overflow, inspections should [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfocus on:  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Functions and code paths in `src/libexif/libexif/exif-data.c`:  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m213[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – `exif_data_load_data_content` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m531[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – `exif_data_load_data` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m984[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – `exif_data_new_from_data` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m159[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. How entry lengths and buffer sizes are computed and validated before the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`memcpy`.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Any related size-check or boundary-check logic in the EXIF parsing routines.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Harness Context  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The provided `exif_from_data_fuzzer` harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_from_data_fuzzer.cc`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m simply [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfeeds arbitrary data into `exif_data_new_from_data`. While the harness is not the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mroot cause, it exposes the overflow by invoking the problematic parsing path with [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmalformed inputs.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis overflow may allow an attacker to read or overwrite adjacent heap data when [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessing crafted EXIF data streams. Further review of size calculations and [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmemory copying in the noted functions is required for a comprehensive assessment.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m206[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m  [0m[32m"Tag data goes past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdoff+s, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m207[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m208[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m209[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m210[0m[39m:    [0m[39mentry->data = exif_data_alloc [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m211[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m212[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mentry->size = s;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m213[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mmemcpy [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m214[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m215[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[1;35mEXIF_LOG_NO_MEMORY[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m216[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m217[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m218[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m219[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* If this is the MakerNote, remember the offset *[0m[35m/[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m220[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->tag == EXIF_TAG_MAKER_NOTE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m221[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!entry->data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m222[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m223[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m  [0m[32m"MakerNote found with empty data"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;   [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m224[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->size > [0m[1;36m6[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m225[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log,[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m226[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m       EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m227[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m       [0m[32m"MakerNote found [0m[32m([0m[32m%02x %02x %02x [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m%02x "[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m228[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m       [0m[32m"%02x %02x %02x...[0m[32m)[0m[32m."[0m[39m,[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m229[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m       entry->data[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, entry->data[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry->data[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m][0m[39m,[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m230[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m       entry->data[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m3[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, entry->data[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry->data[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m5[0m[1;39m][0m[39m,[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m231[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m       entry->data[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m6[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m232[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m233[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mdata->priv->offset_mnote = doff;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m234[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m235[0m[39m:    [0m[39mreturn [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m236[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibexif/exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:197[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m204[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m197[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Sanity checks *[0m[35m/[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m198[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff >= size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m199[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m200[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m  [0m[32m"Tag starts past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, doff, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m201[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m202[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m203[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m204[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibexif/exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:209[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m214[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m209[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m210[0m[39m:    [0m[39mentry->data = exif_data_alloc [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m211[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m212[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mentry->size = s;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m213[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mmemcpy [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m214[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Identification  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The heap-buffer-overflow originates in `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`src/libexif/libexif/exif-data.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The function computes:  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `s`, the number of bytes to copy [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mformat[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m * [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomponents`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `doff`, the offset into the input buffer `d`.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   It then uses two separate checks:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff >= size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   However, complex interactions of unsigned arithmetic and boundary values can [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mslip past these guards, causing `[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to read off the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mend of the input buffer or write past the allocation.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Strategy to Eliminate the Overflow  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Replace the two existing guards with a single, overflow-safe check on the sum[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`doff + s`. This ensures that any case where the requested copy would exceed the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minput buffer is caught—including integer-wrap and edge conditions.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Use the combined expression in an unsigned context to prevent wraparound:  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* BEFORE:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff >= size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* AFTER: *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff + s > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   [0m[32m"Tag data goes past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, doff + s, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Leave the allocation and `memcpy` logic intact:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      entry->data = [0m[1;35mexif_data_alloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          entry->size = s;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mEXIF_LOG_NO_MEMORY[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This patch guarantees that copying `s` bytes from `d + doff` is always within [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe bounds of the input buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m .. size-[0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and that the destination was [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocated for exactly `s` bytes.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Preservation of Existing Functionality  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The new check remains logically equivalent to the prior two, except it also [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrules out subtle corner‐cases [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `doff + s` integer overflow[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Valid entries where `doff + s == size` still pass [0m[1;39m([0m[39mreading/writing up to the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlast byte[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other code paths or data structures are touched; all downstream logic in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_content`, `exif_data_load_data`, and `exif_data_new_from_data`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontinues unchanged.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Testing & Validation  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Rebuild the library and rerun `exif_from_data_fuzzer`. The ASan overflow at [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry` should no longer trigger.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run existing regression tests to ensure no functionality regressions.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Optionally, add a small corpus entry with a crafted IFD entry at the very end [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof the buffer to verify it’s now rejected cleanly without crashing.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential Side-Effects & Mitigation  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stricter boundary check may reject some borderline inputs that previously [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsed a zero‐length remainder entry. However, reading exactly up to `size` was [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mitself precarious; this patch prevents any off-by-one.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If downstream logic relies on parsing zero‐length data entries at buffer [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39medges, a future enhancement could be to explicitly accept `s == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m` or log it as a [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwarning. At present, `s == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m` is already handled earlier in the function [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms ==[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Summary  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   By consolidating the two separate checks into a single robust `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff + s > [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` guard, we eliminate the heap‐buffer‐overflow without impacting legitimate [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mEXIF parsing. This approach follows in-tree patterns for boundary validation and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmaintains compatibility with the existing fuzzer harness and test suite.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is an AddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow triggered inside [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_data_load_data_entry [0m[1;39m([0m[39min libexif/exif-data.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. A malformed EXIF data block [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcauses memcpy to read past the end of a heap buffer allocated to hold the entry’s [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontents.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch attempt collapsed two separate boundary checks—[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff >= size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;`[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;`[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m—into a single check:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff + s > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mlog[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m [0m[32m"Tag data goes past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, doff + s, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch and rerunning the fuzzer, the same heap-buffer-overflow [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrecurs at a slightly shifted line number, indicating the fix did not prevent the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mout-of-bounds read.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer entry point [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m calls [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_new_from_data`, which eventually invokes `exif_data_load_data_entry`.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `exif_data_load_data_entry`, two values are computed:[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - `doff = offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m`, an offset into the input buffer.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - `s`, the size of the data payload for the EXIF tag.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The code originally performed two separate checks:[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff >= size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Despite these guards, an invocation occurs where `doff < size` but `doff + s > [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize`, causing `memcpy` to read `s` bytes past the buffer end.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer report excerpt:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mREAD of size [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m at [0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m thread T0[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m  in __asan_memcpy … exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:213:3[0m[39m in exif_data_load_data_entry[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m…[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m is located [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes after [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte region [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x511000000180[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis confirms the payload length `s` pushes the read past the [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte allocation.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch replaced the two-step validation with a single combined check. Diff [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maround line ~[0m[1;36m195[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m207[0m[39m:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```diff[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--- a/libexif/exif-data.c[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+++ b/libexif/exif-data.c[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m@@ [0m[1;36m-195[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m15[0m[39m +[0m[1;36m195[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m9[0m[39m @@[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    doff = offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-   [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Sanity checks *[0m[35m/[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff >= size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-       [0m[1;35mlog[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m [0m[32m"Tag starts past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, doff, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-       return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-       [0m[1;35mlog[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m [0m[32m"Tag data goes past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, doff + s, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+   [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Sanity check combined *[0m[35m/[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff + s > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+       [0m[1;35mlog[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m [0m[32m"Tag data goes past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, doff + s, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+       return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo other code paths were adjusted; after this change, the code still attempts the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msame `memcpy`.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Result[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter rebuilding and rerunning the fuzzer [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m100[0m[39m runs[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, AddressSanitizer reports the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentical heap-buffer-overflow, now at exif-data.c line [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m==ERROR: AddressSanitizer: heap-buffer-overflow in exif_data_load_data_entry[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m… read of size [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m at [0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m …[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSUMMARY: AddressSanitizer: heap-buffer-overflow exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:207:3[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe failure shows that despite the new combined check, the code path still reaches [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`memcpy` with out-of-bounds parameters.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Further Investigation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo fully understand and address the overflow, the following parts of the codebase [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould be reviewed:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Offset and Size Computation**  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The logic that reads `offset` and computes `doff = offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m`.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Potential integer overflow when adding `offset` and `[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m` on very large `offset`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalues.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Payload Length [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`s`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Determination**  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How `s` is assigned, especially for unsupported or corrupted tag types.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether `s` ever underflows or overruns its intended maximum.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Memory Allocation for the Entry**  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The size passed to `malloc` or `new` for the buffer in which the EXIF data is [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstored.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any assumptions about maximum data length.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Related Routines in exif_data_load_data_content and exif_data_load_data**  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Higher-level loops that drive calls to `exif_data_load_data_entry`.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any missing or misplaced bounds checks prior to entry handling.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Logging and Early Returns**  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensuring that every path that could lead to an out-of-bounds read is correctly[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguarded by an early return.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA holistic fix will require auditing all code paths that handle buffer offsets, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlengths, and allocations in libexif’s data-loading functions.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ [0m[33mFUZZER[0m[39m=[0m[35mexif_from_data_fuzzer[0m                                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m172[0m[39m:    [0m[39mentry->components = exif_get_long  [0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m173[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m174[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* FIXME: should use exif_tag_get_name_in_ifd here but entry->parent [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m175[0m[39m:    [0m[39m * has not been set yet[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The current guard `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff + s > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` uses `unsigned int` arithmetic, so [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen `doff + s` exceeds `UINT_MAX` it wraps around, allowing an oversized copy to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproceed and trigger a heap-buffer-overflow.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The original two-step checks [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`doff >= size` and `s > size - doff`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m prevented [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwraparound by ensuring every subtraction/addition happened in bounded unsigned [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marithmetic, but they were removed in the last patch.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We must reintroduce a boundary check that cannot be bypassed by [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m-bit wrap, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout changing the fuzzer harness or external interfaces.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Strategy Overview[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replace the single [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m-bit addition check with a wrap-proof boundary check:[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Either revert to the original two-step checks:[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ‑ if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff >= size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ‑ if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Or perform the combined check in a wider integer type [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`size_t`[0m[35m/[0m[95m64-bit[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to avoid wrap:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ‑ `size_t end = [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mdoff + [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39ms;`[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ‑ `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mend > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;`[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We recommend the combined safe check using `size_t` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mapproach b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m because it is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconcise and clearly eliminates wrap possibilities.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Detailed Patch Steps[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Locate exif_data_load_data_entry in libexif/exif-data.c, around lines [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m192[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m207[0m[39m.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Remove the incorrect [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m-bit check block:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff + s > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mlog[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Insert the wrap-proof check immediately after calculating `doff` and `s`:[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            size_t end = [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mdoff + [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39ms;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mend > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                         [0m[32m"Tag data goes past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%zu > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m,[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                         end, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Note: We use `%zu` for the [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit `end` and retain `%u` for `size`, logging [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboth values.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This single check covers both “start past end” and “payload too large” cases, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand is immune to [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m-bit overflow.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m No other code paths related to harness, tests, or external libraries need [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmodification.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preservation of Existing Functionality[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We do not alter the logic that computes `s` or `doff`, nor the downstream [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`memcpy` or data handling.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing early returns for zero-length or invalid formats remain intact.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fuzzing harness and tests see the same API; only internal boundary validation [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis hardened.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Addressing Potential Side-Effects[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Introducing `size_t` requires no new includes [0m[1;39m([0m[39malready standard in C [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodebases[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The logging format adjustment [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`%zu`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is compatible with C99+. If the project [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtargets older standards, cast `end` back to `unsigned long` and use `%lu`.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Performance impact is negligible: one [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit addition and comparison per tag [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This solution directly fixes the integer-wrap vulnerability that allowed the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - It keeps code minimal, readable, and maintains existing behavior for all valid[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mEXIF data.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Similar patterns [0m[1;39m([0m[39musing `size_t` to avoid arithmetic wrap[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m can be found [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39melsewhere for safe memcpy bounds checks.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By centralizing the check in one spot, we reduce duplicated logic and [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meliminate the risk of partially applied patches.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. No Further Iteration Required[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After this change, rerunning the fuzzer should no longer trigger the overflow [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:207[0m[39m.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No modifications to harness or test code are necessary.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This completes a holistic fix for the described issue.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
