[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe libexif fuzz target [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_from_data_fuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m triggers an AddressSanitizer [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow in `exif_data_load_data_entry`. The overflow occurs when [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreading up to [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes from a calculated data offset that runs past the end of a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msmall input buffer.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA patch was applied to add two boundary checks around the external offset field [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m byte tag header[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and to unify the later data-range check with a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff, size, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` macro. After rebuilding with the patch, the same [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mASan heap-buffer-overflow reappeared at a slightly shifted line number in [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry`, indicating the overflow is still unhandled.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fuzzer log shows a crash in `__asan_memcpy` inside `exif_data_load_data_entry`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen copying `s` bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39min this case [0m[1;36m16[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m from `d + doff`.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The offending address `[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m` is exactly one byte past a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregion [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x180[0m[39m … [0m[1;36m0x24f[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, i.e. `doff + s` exceeds the buffer length.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Call stack:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. exif_data_load_data_entry [0m[1;39m([0m[39msrc/libexif/libexif/exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:213[0m[1;39m)[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. exif_data_load_data_content[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. exif_data_load_data[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. exif_data_new_from_data[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No prior bounds checks prevented reading beyond the buffer when the field size[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`s > [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m189[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the code was reorganized:[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * If `s > [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`, before computing the external data offset:[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       - Add `[0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset, size, [0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to prevent reading the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte offset[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ the [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-byte header past the buffer end.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       - If it would overflow, log a debug message and `return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m`.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       - Otherwise compute `doff = [0m[1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Else [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`s <= [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, treat data as inline, `doff = offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m`.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Then, in both cases, a final unified check `[0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff, size, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwas inserted:[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       - If the requested range `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdoff..doff+s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` lies outside the buffer of length [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`size`, log and `return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m`.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch used this macro and logging call:[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff, size, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m,[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                  [0m[32m"Tag data goes past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u + %u > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m,[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                  doff, s, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Result after patch  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer run still aborts with ASan reporting a heap-buffer-overflow at the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msame `exif-data.c` function [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnow at line [0m[1;36m216[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The shadow memory and heap allocation details are nearly identical, showing [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe attempt to guard did not prevent the read of [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes at the boundary.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This indicates either:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * The `CHECKOVERFLOW` invocations do not correctly detect the overflow [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcondition in all cases.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * There may be multiple code paths or other memcpy calls in the same function [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat lack checks.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for further investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The definition and behavior of the `[0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39ma, b, c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` macro: ensure it [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcorrectly flags `a + c > b` especially when `a + c` or intermediate sums wrap or [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare unsigned.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All places in `exif_data_load_data_entry` where `memcpy` or `exif_get_long` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreads from `d + doff`: verify each read is preceded by a correct bounds check.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The calculation of `s`, `offset`, and `doff` to confirm they always represent [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min-bounds ranges [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. ensure no signed/unsigned mismatch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The two branches [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`s > [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m` vs. inline[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and any shared code after them: confirm [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mno other early returns skip the unified check.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Neighboring code in `exif_data_load_data_content` and the caller [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data`, in case they supply inconsistent `size` or `data` pointers [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat affect bounds assumptions.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
